==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Italian ''ocarina'', literally "little goose", due to the musical instrument's resemblance to the animal.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{musici}} A [[woodwind]] musical instrument that is closed at both sides to produce an enclosed space, and punctured with finger holes.

